01:52.281 --> 01:53.993
This was amazing,

01:53.993 --> 01:56.999
because three months earlier,
I myself had had a dream

01:56.999 --> 02:01.507
about a man carrying
a pregnant woman through fire.

02:01.507 --> 02:03.511
So, when I overhear this man‐‐

02:03.511 --> 02:05.683
this custodian
in one of my hotels,

02:05.683 --> 02:09.608
a man I have never spoken to
or met in my life‐‐

02:09.608 --> 02:14.450
talking about a man saving
a woman from fire,

02:14.450 --> 02:17.289
it was abundantly
clear to me...

02:17.289 --> 02:22.257
that something remarkable was
presenting itself to me.

02:22.257 --> 02:24.011
Two days later,

02:24.011 --> 02:26.934
I attended my first
Meyerist meeting.

02:26.934 --> 02:29.230
There were hundreds
of people there.

02:29.230 --> 02:31.860
I was overjoyed and shocked.

02:31.860 --> 02:35.743
There were villagers,
shop owners, young kids,

02:35.743 --> 02:37.956
and even a few stiffs
in suits like me.

02:37.956 --> 02:40.460
‐

02:40.460 --> 02:43.007
‐ That night...

02:43.007 --> 02:46.389
was the first time I saw images

02:46.389 --> 02:49.729
of this mythical American...

02:49.729 --> 02:51.357
Eddie Lane.

02:53.152 --> 02:56.869
And when I was first introduced
to The Ladder...

02:58.246 --> 03:00.960
From that moment on...

03:00.960 --> 03:05.427
all I have ever wanted
was to climb.

03:05.427 --> 03:08.391
But, um, we've never
done any outreach

03:08.391 --> 03:10.521
in Asia‐‐none.
‐ I know.

03:10.521 --> 03:12.650
Believe me, I know.

03:12.650 --> 03:15.488
I've long been skeptical
of these missionaries

03:15.488 --> 03:17.785
preying on our people.

03:17.785 --> 03:19.330
When I first encountered
Meyerism,

03:19.330 --> 03:22.419
I was looking for the scam‐‐
the illusion,

03:22.419 --> 03:25.718
the explanation, the strings.

03:25.718 --> 03:30.352
‐ Every so often,
things just happen.

03:30.352 --> 03:32.481
‐ It happened...

03:32.481 --> 03:35.236
because
it cannot be stopped.

03:35.236 --> 03:38.326
The message is spreading...

03:38.326 --> 03:40.288
which is why I...

03:40.288 --> 03:44.088
invited you all here tonight.

03:44.088 --> 03:49.348
This is my resort property
on Kuta Beach.

03:49.348 --> 03:51.728
I would like,
with your permission,

03:51.728 --> 03:56.195
to convert it into the first
Meyerist Center in Asia.

03:56.195 --> 03:57.782
The logistics are under way.

03:57.782 --> 04:00.370
I was too giddy to wait,
I must admit.

04:02.416 --> 04:05.338
And if we stay on schedule,

04:05.338 --> 04:08.094
I would like to unveil it
to you‐‐

04:08.094 --> 04:10.766
to the world...

04:10.766 --> 04:13.689
on the next hunter's moon,
next month.

04:13.689 --> 04:15.818
‐
‐ I'll go.

04:15.818 --> 04:17.572
I mean, look at these beaches.

04:17.572 --> 04:18.824
‐ Right.

04:18.824 --> 04:22.707
‐ I would like
our countrymen...

04:22.707 --> 04:25.170
to learn everything
that Steven Meyer learned

04:25.170 --> 04:27.090
from The Light.

04:27.090 --> 04:28.802
‐ Um... well...

04:28.802 --> 04:32.100
Everything, um, learned
from The Light

04:32.100 --> 04:34.396
belongs to Eddie Lane now.

04:34.396 --> 04:38.321
Anything to be learned
will be taught by Eddie.

04:38.321 --> 04:39.783
‐ Hmm.

04:42.789 --> 04:44.500
‐ To The Light in Bali.

04:44.500 --> 04:48.634
To The Light in Bali.

04:50.095 --> 04:53.017
My mother always told me
that The Movement's growth

04:53.017 --> 04:55.564
would lead to its collapse.

04:57.067 --> 04:59.948
‐ So you're saying
that Bali is a bad idea?

04:59.948 --> 05:01.868
‐ No, um...

05:01.868 --> 05:05.584
‐ Look, Vera, you're not
under your mother's thumb...

05:05.584 --> 05:07.170
anymore.

05:07.170 --> 05:08.590
‐ Yeah, I know that.

05:08.590 --> 05:10.678
It's hard to hear someone be

05:10.678 --> 05:15.353
so 100% certain
about something so terrifying.

05:15.353 --> 05:18.234
‐ Ah, I get that,
but, hey, look,

05:18.234 --> 05:21.323
whatever happens
is going to happen.

05:21.323 --> 05:23.035
I mean, I didn't have
anything to do

05:23.035 --> 05:26.585
with introducing Meyerism
to Bali, but here we are.

05:26.585 --> 05:29.716
I mean, we're going
to fucking Bali.

05:29.716 --> 05:32.304
All right?

05:32.304 --> 05:34.266
Come on.

05:34.266 --> 05:36.855
‐ Hey, Eddie.

05:36.855 --> 05:40.236
Do you‐‐do you think
we'll recover?

05:41.698 --> 05:42.909
‐ Vera.

05:42.909 --> 05:44.913
‐ Yeah, I know. I'm...

05:44.913 --> 05:47.710
I'm sorry. It's just...

05:47.710 --> 05:49.672
y‐you look at me differently.

05:49.672 --> 05:51.258
‐ Hey.

05:51.258 --> 05:53.262
Look, I just don't know
how to look at you

05:53.262 --> 05:56.060
and not make it...

05:56.060 --> 05:57.855
you know, different.

05:59.191 --> 06:02.239
You know, I don't know how
to keep talking about this

06:02.239 --> 06:03.867
or not keep talking about this.

06:03.867 --> 06:05.203
I'm just...

06:05.203 --> 06:06.790
processing.

06:06.790 --> 06:08.585
That's all. Okay?

06:08.585 --> 06:11.090
That's just gonna
take some time.

06:11.090 --> 06:13.261
Okay?
So just give me that.

06:13.261 --> 06:15.683
It's gonna be... great.

06:15.683 --> 06:18.522
‐ Yeah. It will.

06:18.522 --> 06:20.358
‐ It will.

06:20.358 --> 06:22.195
Come here.

06:24.324 --> 06:26.370
We're both wiped.

06:26.370 --> 06:31.088
You have the AL tomorrow.
Let's just get some rest.

06:31.088 --> 06:33.092
‐ Yeah, that'll be good.

06:33.092 --> 06:35.138
‐ Absolutely.

06:37.017 --> 06:38.895
‐ I think there's
someone in there.

06:40.566 --> 06:41.651
‐
Wait, wait, wait.

06:41.651 --> 06:43.446
Stay here.
Okay?

06:43.446 --> 06:45.408
‐ Yeah.
‐ Good.

07:01.983 --> 07:03.110
Jesus!

07:03.110 --> 07:04.446
Hawk!
‐ I'm sorry.

07:04.446 --> 07:05.699
I‐I thought‐‐
‐ What?

07:05.699 --> 07:07.243
‐
I need your keys.

07:07.243 --> 07:09.164
I was looking for your keys
to the Prius lot.

07:09.164 --> 07:11.836
‐ Why didn't you ask first
before breaking in?

07:11.836 --> 07:13.380
‐ 'Cause I thought
you'd say no.

07:13.380 --> 07:16.261
‐ Say no to what?

07:16.261 --> 07:19.226
‐ I got a letter.
It's from Caleb.

07:19.226 --> 07:20.979
Well, I mean, it's not‐‐
it's "from Caleb,"

07:20.979 --> 07:25.154
but it's not from Caleb.
It's...

07:25.154 --> 07:27.910
‐ Hey, Hawk.
‐ Hi, Vera.

07:29.539 --> 07:31.458
‐ Look...

07:31.458 --> 07:33.797
I can tell that you're...

07:33.797 --> 07:36.886
very torn up about whatever's
happening with Caleb.

07:36.886 --> 07:39.099
But you have to promise me

07:39.099 --> 07:42.272
that you will not do
anything like this again.

07:44.151 --> 07:46.321
‐ Yeah.
Okay.

07:46.321 --> 07:48.450
‐ Okay?
‐ Yeah.

07:48.450 --> 07:50.873
Just... read it.

07:58.805 --> 08:01.393
I mean, there's no way
he wrote that.

08:01.393 --> 08:03.189
"I ask you as a friend

08:03.189 --> 08:06.361
to respect my decision
to better myself."

08:06.361 --> 08:09.994
"My commitment to The Light
of this World, Jesus Christ."

08:09.994 --> 08:11.831
What the fuck is that?

08:11.831 --> 08:16.758
He's in trouble there, Dad,
and I have to go help him.

08:16.758 --> 08:19.512
‐ Where?

08:19.512 --> 08:21.141
Maryland?

08:22.477 --> 08:24.941
‐ I need a car.

08:43.102 --> 08:44.897
‐

09:19.424 --> 09:21.554
Five minutes
means five minutes.

09:21.554 --> 09:25.102
500 bucks means five minutes.

09:25.102 --> 09:27.482
‐ How long did you say
since she's been here?

09:27.482 --> 09:31.239
‐ I have no idea.
Where are you going?

09:31.239 --> 09:32.785
Hey!
Hey, hey, hey.

09:32.785 --> 09:34.412
‐ Can you get in the mailbox?

09:34.412 --> 09:36.668
‐ Are you fucking
kidding me, lady?

09:38.337 --> 09:40.676
I'm serious.
Don't push me on this, lady.

09:42.680 --> 09:45.519
Lady, I swear to God...

09:45.519 --> 09:47.523
Are you listening?
Hey, I'm over here!

09:51.989 --> 09:52.991
We're done.
That's it.

09:52.991 --> 09:55.287
Time's up.

09:55.287 --> 09:57.668
I'm talking to you.
Listen to me.

09:57.668 --> 09:59.003
You're out.
We're done.

09:59.003 --> 10:00.005
Let's go.

10:00.005 --> 10:02.009
Now.

10:02.009 --> 10:05.307
Now! Right now! Out!

10:14.910 --> 10:16.496
All right, so this is

10:16.496 --> 10:18.543
what's on the schedule
for the next couple days.

10:18.543 --> 10:20.296
We rescheduled
that podcast thing,

10:20.296 --> 10:21.758
so don't worry about that.
‐ Uh‐huh.

10:21.758 --> 10:23.887
‐ And I'm still getting
some blowback

10:23.887 --> 10:26.308
about the arbitration
contracts.

10:26.308 --> 10:29.690
So, if that flares up
for whatever reason,

10:29.690 --> 10:31.569
just give me a call.

10:31.569 --> 10:33.447
‐ No, if anything comes up,
I'll call you.

10:33.447 --> 10:36.036
‐ Not because I need to know
anything about it, but just...

10:36.036 --> 10:37.539
I don't want you to feel

10:37.539 --> 10:39.585
that you have to put out
these fires on your own.

10:39.585 --> 10:41.296
Not that there's gonna
be any fires,

10:41.296 --> 10:43.843
but just if there are.
‐ I understand.

10:43.843 --> 10:45.262
‐ All right, then.

10:45.262 --> 10:48.645
Um, should be gone just a day,
two tops.

10:48.645 --> 10:50.774
‐ Just you and Hawk?
‐ Yeah.

10:50.774 --> 10:53.487
‐ Nice.
‐ Well, it's, um...

10:53.487 --> 10:57.245
it's Caleb‐related.

10:57.245 --> 10:59.750
His folks sent him

10:59.750 --> 11:03.800
to one of those Christian
re‐education places.

11:03.800 --> 11:05.804
‐ Oh. That is horrible.

11:05.804 --> 11:07.683
It's‐‐that's criminal.

11:07.683 --> 11:10.730
‐ Yeah, well, it should be.
‐ Yeah, it should be.

11:10.730 --> 11:13.485
‐ I don't know what we're
really getting ourselves into,

11:13.485 --> 11:15.991
but, uh, Hawk's pretty adamant.

11:15.991 --> 11:19.038
You know, he has
to talk to him, has to try.

11:19.038 --> 11:21.418
‐ That's really admirable.

11:21.418 --> 11:23.422
‐ Yeah, I agree.

11:23.422 --> 11:25.259
‐ No, I mean‐‐
I mean of you.

11:25.259 --> 11:26.469
‐ Oh, well, no.
‐ It is.

11:26.469 --> 11:28.641
It is.

11:28.641 --> 11:30.979
Even change you believe in
is hard.

11:30.979 --> 11:32.649
You know,
I'm impressed...

11:32.649 --> 11:35.864
father to father.

11:35.864 --> 11:37.701
‐ Thank you.

11:37.701 --> 11:39.955
That's nice of you to say.

11:39.955 --> 11:42.628
Oh, one last thing.

11:42.628 --> 11:46.092
It's the only
special instruction.

11:46.092 --> 11:50.517
Vera is taking
an accelerated AL.

11:50.517 --> 11:52.940
You know, I was
gonna facilitate,

11:52.940 --> 11:55.570
but, you know, she needs this.

11:55.570 --> 11:56.948
‐ Absolutely.

11:56.948 --> 11:58.910
‐ It'd mean a lot to her.

11:58.910 --> 12:01.164
And to me, too.

12:01.164 --> 12:03.460
‐ Of course.

12:03.460 --> 12:05.924
‐ Look...

12:05.924 --> 12:07.761
Cal, I...

12:07.761 --> 12:10.224
trust you completely.

12:10.224 --> 12:11.393
Okay?

12:11.393 --> 12:14.232
I want you to know that.

12:14.232 --> 12:16.696
All right.

12:16.696 --> 12:19.075
Thanks, man.

12:49.803 --> 12:51.514
‐ Hey.
What do you want?

12:51.514 --> 12:52.726
He wants me to
take things over

12:52.726 --> 12:55.732
for a couple of days.

12:55.732 --> 12:58.320
‐ Okay, but you're still gonna
make it to Washington, right?

12:58.320 --> 13:00.992
N‐no, actually, no.
No, I can't.

13:00.992 --> 13:02.746
‐ What?

13:02.746 --> 13:05.835
This is a fucking joke, right?
Harbaugh is expecting us.

13:05.835 --> 13:09.217
‐ I‐I know.
I'm sorry, but this is, um...

13:09.217 --> 13:11.722
You know, I‐I have to stay.

13:11.722 --> 13:14.102
‐ No, you're choosing to.
You're choosing to stay.

13:14.102 --> 13:15.939
You're choosing Eddie over us.

13:15.939 --> 13:18.653
‐
Well, I'll call JP, okay?

13:18.653 --> 13:21.407
I'll call Harbaugh
and, uh‐‐and whoever else

13:21.407 --> 13:22.744
you think I need to call.

13:22.744 --> 13:24.665
I'll handle it.
‐ Oh, you will?

13:24.665 --> 13:27.086
- Okay.
- I will.

13:27.086 --> 13:30.927
And, uh, you know,
I'll grovel, Mary.

13:30.927 --> 13:33.181
You know, I'll them that,
as inconceivable

13:33.181 --> 13:35.144
as it might sound,
the actual Movement

13:35.144 --> 13:37.148
needs my actual attention.

13:37.148 --> 13:39.360
‐ Well, I'm still going.

13:39.360 --> 13:41.991
‐ Um, no‐‐
Well, I mean, I don't know‐‐

13:41.991 --> 13:43.703
I don't know
if that's a good idea.

13:43.703 --> 13:45.748
Harbaugh is‐‐
No, and you there on your own?

13:45.748 --> 13:47.376
‐ Well, I don't think
it's a good idea for you

13:47.376 --> 13:49.046
to do anything
on your own right now,

13:49.046 --> 13:51.635
especially here, what with
all the memory recall

13:51.635 --> 13:55.142
and the weird drawings
of mysterious caves.

13:57.021 --> 13:59.191
- ‐ What about Forest?
- Use the nursery.

13:59.191 --> 14:01.154
We live in a collective
community, remember?

14:11.675 --> 14:13.763
‐

14:15.850 --> 14:17.520
Hey.

14:17.520 --> 14:18.940
‐ I've been calling you
for hours.

14:18.940 --> 14:20.317
Didn't Hawk tell you

14:20.317 --> 14:21.946
that we're driving out
to Maryland?

14:21.946 --> 14:23.699
‐ Yeah, it's‐‐
it's not about that.

14:23.699 --> 14:25.995
- Is he with you now?
- Yeah. He's in the store.

14:25.995 --> 14:27.122
Why?

14:27.122 --> 14:29.085
Is something wrong?

14:29.085 --> 14:32.091
‐ Vera isn't
who she says she is.

14:32.091 --> 14:33.844
‐ Look, I know, okay?

14:33.844 --> 14:36.265
She told me everything.
‐ Wait. You know?

14:36.265 --> 14:39.564
Look, it's really
complicated, Sarah.

14:39.564 --> 14:41.109
‐ Well...

14:41.109 --> 14:43.614
what did she say
she was doing?

14:43.614 --> 14:46.745
‐ She apologized, okay?

14:46.745 --> 14:48.498
And we are trying
to move forward.

14:48.498 --> 14:49.835
Wait. She apologized,

14:49.835 --> 14:51.379
and you didn't think
to tell me?

14:51.379 --> 14:53.759
I've been obsessed
with Lilith for months.

14:53.759 --> 14:57.391
‐ Look, I only just
found this out myself, okay?

14:57.391 --> 14:58.978
Am I supposed
to tell you everything?

14:58.978 --> 15:00.355
‐ Why is she here?

15:00.355 --> 15:04.740
‐ She's becoming
a Meyerist, okay?

15:04.740 --> 15:06.409
Can we just talk
about this later?

15:06.409 --> 15:07.787
Hawk's coming.

15:07.787 --> 15:09.666
Her mother
is missing, Eddie.

15:09.666 --> 15:11.210
Look, I don't know anything

15:11.210 --> 15:13.632
about her mother, okay?
Just let it go.

15:18.058 --> 15:20.020
‐ Who's that?

15:20.020 --> 15:21.481
‐ Your mom says hi.

15:25.740 --> 15:27.409
What did she want?

15:27.409 --> 15:29.998
Just divorce stuff.

15:29.998 --> 15:31.334
It's fine.

15:31.334 --> 15:35.258
Really, it's fine.

15:35.258 --> 15:36.595
‐ It's about Vera?

15:38.014 --> 15:39.183
‐ Mm‐hmm.

15:39.183 --> 15:41.395
‐ Is it real?

15:41.395 --> 15:43.776
‐ What?
‐ You and her.

15:43.776 --> 15:46.239
‐ Yeah, it is.

15:46.239 --> 15:49.328
‐ You don't seem too happy
for a guy in love.

15:52.084 --> 15:54.130
‐ Well, neither do you.

15:57.971 --> 16:00.058
Is that why you came?

16:00.058 --> 16:02.271
Get away from all that stuff?

16:02.271 --> 16:06.655
‐ No, I came because I want
to try to help you out,

16:06.655 --> 16:08.449
if I can.

16:08.449 --> 16:10.328
All right?

16:10.328 --> 16:12.040
It's just...

16:12.040 --> 16:16.550
things have been hard lately
with Vera.

16:16.550 --> 16:18.094
‐ Why?

16:18.094 --> 16:20.223
‐ You just never really know
someone, I guess.

16:20.223 --> 16:22.812
‐ You don't know Vera?

16:22.812 --> 16:24.273
‐ No.

16:24.273 --> 16:28.364
All of us,
we just have so much stuff.

16:28.364 --> 16:30.995
Sometimes that stuff can
make you fall

16:30.995 --> 16:33.667
deeper in love
with that person.

16:33.667 --> 16:36.255
Other times, that stuff...

16:36.255 --> 16:37.717
doesn't make you love
them any less.

16:37.717 --> 16:41.558
It just...

16:41.558 --> 16:45.023
makes you love them
differently.

16:45.023 --> 16:47.987
And that is harder
than it sounds.

16:54.083 --> 16:57.089
‐

16:59.886 --> 17:03.811
‐ Isn't this meant
to be in total darkness?

17:03.811 --> 17:05.564
Hence the term
"Absence of Light"?

17:05.564 --> 17:08.820
Yeah, and typically,
there'd be 20 people with you.

17:08.820 --> 17:11.117
You're doing
the hard‐core version.

17:11.117 --> 17:14.455
But, you know,
this is just a backup.

17:14.455 --> 17:15.751
‐ Hmm.

17:15.751 --> 17:17.755
So, um...

17:17.755 --> 17:20.970
people see things, hmm?

17:20.970 --> 17:22.263
